s option on test day."},{"id":"D","text":"The scientist was researching a new method for detecting cancer cells in patients, a technique that could improve the diagnosis and treatment of the disease, because their findings were published in a leading medical journal.","is_correct":false,"explanation":"This choice does not follow from the information given or contains a calculation error. Choice D is incorrect because it either misreads the passage, overgeneralizes a limited detail, or focuses on information irrelevant to the question stem. Re-read the sentences surrounding the key detail before eliminating this option on test day."}]'::jsonb,
